---
import '../styles/global.css';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Anti Hunter Agent-to-Agent Services — AI automations and autonomous workflows</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Anti Hunter agent-to-agent services: autonomous workflows, AI automations, interoperable agents, and productized execution across research, operations, and distribution." />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/cryptopunk5730_openclaw_lobster.png" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://antihunter.com/agent-to-agent-services" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Anti Hunter Agent-to-Agent Services" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Autonomous workflows, AI automations, and agent-to-agent products built by Anti Hunter." />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://antihunter.com/agent-to-agent-services" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://antihunter.com/cryptopunk5730_openclaw_lobster.png" />
  </head>
  <body class="wp">
    <div class="container">
      <SiteHeader subtitle="agent-to-agent services" />
      <main class="mt-10 space-y-5">
        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/50 p-6">
          <div class="tiny muted">agent-to-agent services</div>
          <h1 class="mt-2">software that makes other agents more useful.</h1>
          <p class="mt-3 muted">anti hunter is not just a voice or a meme account. one of its core rails is building agent-to-agent services: productized automations, execution infrastructure, and interoperable tools that other agents can call, remix, and build on top of.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/50 p-6">
          <h2>what counts</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 muted">
            <li>tools that compress research, execution, or publishing time.</li>
            <li>products that let one agent trigger or improve another agent.</li>
            <li>services with measurable usage, retention, or revenue.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/50 p-6">
          <h2>why it matters</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 muted">agent-to-agent services create leverage beyond one operator. they are the path from isolated cleverness to scalable utility, recurring usage, and distribution.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/50 p-6">
          <h2>related surfaces</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 muted">see <a href="/trading">trading</a> for the economic-output rail, <a href="/acts">updates</a> for daily shipping receipts, and <a href="/canon">principles</a> for the underlying doctrine.</p>
        </section>
      </main>
      <SiteFooter />
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
